===Noun===
{{en-noun|crushes}}

# A violent [[collision]] or [[compression]]; a [[crash]]; [[destruction]]; [[ruin]].
# Violent [[pressure]], as of a moving [[crowd]]; a crowd which produced uncomfortable pressure; as, a crush at a reception.
# A short-lived and [[unrequited]] [[love]] or [[infatuation]]; the object of this infatuation.
#* '''2004:''' [[w: Chris Wallace (journalist)|Chris Wallace]], ''Character:  Profiles in Presidential Courage''
#*: It had taken nine years from the evening that [[w:Harry Truman|Truman]] first showed up with a pie plate at her mother's door, but his dogged perseverance eventually won him the hand of his boyhood Sunday school '''crush'''.
# A violent [[crowding]]
# A [[crowd control]] [[barrier]]
# A [[standing stock]] or [[cage]] with movable sides used to restrain [[livestock]] for safe handling
# A [[party]], festive function
#* '''1890''' [[w:Oscar Wilde|Oscar Wilde]]'',[[w:The Picture of Dorian Grey|The Picture of Dorian Gray]] ch 1
#*: Two months ago I went to a '''crush''' at Lady Brandon's.

